 31s NAME
 31s        stringprep_check_version - API function
 31s 
 31s SYNOPSIS
 31s        #include <stringprep.h>
 31s 
 31s        const char * stringprep_check_version(const char * req_version);
 31s 
 31s ARGUMENTS
 31s        const char * req_version
 31s                    Required version number, or NULL.
 31s 
 31s DESCRIPTION
 31s        Check  that  the version of the library is at minimum the requested one and return the version string; return NULL if the condition is not satis‐
 31s        fied.  If a NULL is passed to this function, no check is done, but the version string is simply returned.
 31s 
 31s        See STRINGPREP_VERSION for a suitable  req_version string.
 31s 
 31s        Return value: Version string of run-time library, or NULL if the run-time library does not meet the required version number.
